title: diluc_(genshin_impact)
body:
A [[Genshin Impact]] character.

The current owner of the Dawn Winery, Diluc was once a member of the Knights of Favonius until a past tragedy has caused him to resign in the Knights' ranks. Despite this, he continues to protect Mondstadt as the mysterious rumored "[spoiler]Darknight Hero[/spoiler]".

title: keqing_(genshin_impact)
body:
A playable Electro character in [[Genshin Impact]].

A workaholic even at her young age, she serves as the Yuheng for the Liyue Qixing.

Her name is pronounced [b]Kokusei[/b] in the Japanese version of the game.

She appears in [[Honkai Impact 3rd]], as a story event-only character. 

Voiced by [[Kitamura Eri]] (Japanese).

title: ai_hyperion_lambda
body:
A [i][[Honkai Impact 3rd]][/i] character, serving as the in-game assistant to the [[Entropy (honkai impact)|Dreamseeker]] for Part 2. A time crystal entity unrelated to [[Ai-chan (honkai_impact)|Ai-chan]] despite their similar appearance. Voiced by [[Horie Yui]] in Japanese. 

She is still portrayed with the same [[long hair|long]] [[green hair]] tied into [[double bun]]s, and [[orange eyes]], but has a mature and taller physique with [[large breasts]]. She uses a [[chakram]] as her main weapon.

[[Thighhighs]] that have a ribbed pattern, creating the appearance of vertical stripes.

Not to be confused with [[vertical-striped thighhighs]] or [[pinstripe thighhighs]].

title: ribbed_sleeves
body: A pair of sleeves that have a ribbed pattern. The sleeves have to either be [[detached sleeves|detached]], or differently patterned from the rest of the garment the character is wearing (such as [[raglan sleeves]]).

title: ribbed_panties
body:
[[Panties]] that have a ribbed pattern, creating the appearance of vertical stripes.

Not to be confused with [[vertical-striped panties]].

title: butterfree
body:
[[pokemon_(creature)|Pokémon]] #0012 in the National Pokédex, a Bug/Flying-type.

Resembles a vaguely anthropomorphic [[butterfly]] with a purple body. It has two black [[antennae]], a light blue snout with two [[fangs]] underneath, and large, [[red_eyes|red]] [[compound eyes]]. Its two pairs of veined [[insect_wings|wings]] are white with black accents.

Evolves from [[Metapod]] (from [[Caterpie]]). It also has a [[Gigantamax]] form.

Japanese name: [b]Butterfree[/b]

h4. Official art
* !asset #25145768: Butterfree
* !asset #25145770: [[Gigantamax Butterfree]]

h4. External links

* "Bulbapedia":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Butterfree_%28Pokémon%29

Prior Pokémon: [[Metapod]]
Next Pokémon: [[Weedle]]

title: pidgeot
body:
[[pokemon_(creature)|Pokémon]] #0018 in the National Pokédex, a Normal/Flying-type.

An avian Pokémon with large [[wings]], sharp [[talons]], and a short, hooked [[beak]]. Its glossy plumage is mostly brown with cream-colored underparts and flight feathers. Its head is decorated with a red and yellow crest that is nearly as long as its body. The fan-like feathers of its tail are red. Its beak and legs are pink, and there are angular black markings around its eyes.

Evolves from [[Pidgeotto]] (from [[Pidgey]]). It can also [[mega_pokemon|Mega Evolve]].

Japanese name: [b]Pigeot[/b]

h4. Official art
* !asset #25145778: Pidgeot
* !asset #25145774: [[Mega Pidgeot]]

h4. External links

* "Bulbapedia":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pidgeot_%28Pokémon%29

Prior Pokémon: [[Pidgeotto]]
Next Pokémon: [[Rattata]]

title: charizard
body:
[[pokemon_(creature)|Pokémon]] #0006 in the National Pokédex, a Fire/Flying-type starter.

A large, draconic creature with [[horns]], [[wings]], and a [[flame-tipped_tail|flaming tail tip]].

Evolves from [[Charmeleon]] (from [[Charmander]]). It can both [[mega_pokemon|Mega Evolve]] and [[Gigantamax]].

Playable in the [[Super Smash Bros.]] series, as one of three Pokémon used by the Pokémon Trainer in Brawl and Ultimate, and as a solo character in Smash 4.

Japanese name: [b]Lizardon[/b]

title: mighty_morphin_alien_rangers
body: The second series in Saban's [[Power Rangers]] franchise. Adapts stock footage from [[Ninja Sentai Kakuranger]] along with largely newly filmed footage, and follows directly after the events of the third season of [[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers]]. In tandem with its 10-episode season length, it is officially considered a mini-series and 'Season 3.5' of Mighty Morphin, with [[Power Rangers Zeo]] being the first full series following Mighty Morphin.
other_names: マイティ・モーフィン・エイリアンレンジャー
エイリアンレンジャー

title: lord_zedd
body:
One of the main antagonists for [[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers]] and [[Power Rangers Cosmic Fury]], and one of the first Ranger-exclusive villains.

He would debut as [[Witch Bandora|Rita Repulsa]]'s superior, eventually rebanishing her as to take control of operations against the Rangers, though she would return to give him a love potion and make him her husband.

title: nidoran_(female)

title: ciel_(tsukihime)
body:
A character in the visual novel and anime series [[Tsukihime]], who also makes an appearance in the 2d fighting game [[Melty Blood]].

She is voiced by [[Orikasa Fumiko]] in the original Tsukihime anime, by [[Wendee Lee]] in the English dub, [[Sakuma Kumi]] in Melty Blood, and [[Hondo Kaede]] in the [[Tsukihime (remake)|2021 remake]]. Ciel also makes an appearance in [[Kagetsu Tooya]] as [[ciel-sensei|Ciel Sensei]], where she acts as a teacher to various Tsukihime characters, among them [[Neco-Arc]].

Her birthday is May 3rd. Her height is 165, weighs 52 kg with a blood type of O. Her three sizes are B85/W56/H88. She appears to be a teenager, but her true age is much older, and unknown.

In the original Tsukihime she has [[curtained hair]], whereas in the remake she has [[hair between eyes|bangs between her eyes]].

title: shimada_arisu
body:
A character from the series [[Girls und Panzer]] introduced in the [[girls_und_panzer_gekijouban|Der Film]].

Tank commander of a [[Centurion (tank)|Centurion]] and overall commander of the "Selection University":[#dtext-see-also] tankery team.

Voiced by [[Taketatsu Ayana]] "[1]":[#dtext-external-links].

[expand=Official Character Bio]

h5. Selection University Team

h6. Der Film

Overall commander for the Selection University team. A genius girl who skipped grades all the way to college. As a daughter of the school head for the Shimada tankery school, she has a natural ability to command at tankery. She is a big fan of Boko, and she meets Miho at the Boko museum before the match. Personally commands an A41 Centurion.

[tn]Source: "[2]":[#dtext-external-links][/tn]

title: pidgeotto
body:
[[pokemon_(creature)|Pokémon]] #0017 in the National Pokédex, a Normal/Flying-type.

A raptor-like avian Pokémon. It is covered with [[brown feathers]], and has a cream-colored face and underside. It has a crest of pinkish-red feathers on its head and black, angular markings behind its eyes. The plumage of its tail has alternating [[red_feathers|red]] and [[yellow feathers]] with ragged tips. Its beak and legs are pink, and it has sharp [[talons]].

Evolves from [[Pidgey]], and into [[Pidgeot]].

Japanese name: [b]Pigeon[/b]

title: playstation_vita
body:
The [b]PlayStation Vita[/b] (プレイステーション・ヴィータ, officially abbreviated PS Vita) is a handheld game console manufactured and marketed by Sony Computer Entertainment. 

It is the successor to the [[PlayStation Portable]] as part of the PlayStation series. 

The PS Vita was released in Japan and parts of Asia on December 17, 2011, in Europe, North America, South America and Singapore on February 22, 2012 and in Australia on February 23, 2012. 

It primarily competes with the [[Nintendo 3DS]] as part of the eighth generation of gaming.

Software for the PlayStation Vita is distributed on a proprietary flash memory card called "PlayStation Vita card" rather than on Universal Media Discs (UMDs) as used by the PlayStation Portable.

The handheld includes two analog sticks, an OLED multi-touch capacitive touchscreen, and supports Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and optional 3G. Internally, the Vita features a four-core ARM Cortex-A9 MPCore processor and a four-core SGX543MP4+ graphics processing unit, as well as LiveArea software as its main user interface, which succeeds the XrossMediaBar.

body:
An orbital ring is a [[megastructure]]. A ring (or many) floating in space tethered to earth or any planetary surface via [[space elevator]]s which can function as access points to the ring for transportation or power transmission.

Not to be confused to [[orbital path]] where an orbit is drawn with a ring.

h4. See also

title: space_elevator
body:
A [b]space elevator[/b] is a proposed type of [[space]] transportation system. Like its name implies, is basically an elevator designed to ascend all the way through the atmosphere and into space.

Its main component is a ribbon-like cable (also called a tether) anchored to the surface and extending into space. It is designed to permit vehicle transport along the cable from a planetary surface, such as the Earth's, directly into space or orbit, without the use of large [[rocket]]s.

The key concept behind the space elevator was first introduced in 1895 by Russian scientist "Konstantin Tsiolkovsky":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Konstantin_Tsiolkovsky who was inspired by the construction of the [[Eiffel Tower]] from Paris, France.

The system is also referred as the orbital elevator, Jacob's Ladder and Beanstalk in several old [[science fiction]] stories. The related concepts are the [[space fountain]], [[orbital ring]], skyhook, space necklace and rotovator.

title: playstation_3
body:
The [b]PlayStation 3[/b] (プレイステーション3, Pureisutēshon Surī?, officially abbreviated as "PS3") is the third home [[video game]] [[game console|console]] produced by [[Sony]] Computer Entertainment and the successor to the [[PlayStation 2]] as part of the PlayStation series. 

The PlayStation 3 competes with [[Microsoft]]'s [[Xbox 360]] and [[Nintendo]]'s [[Wii]] as part of the seventh generation of video game consoles. Its big, heavy and low capacity first model was first released on November 11, 2006, in Japan, with international markets following shortly thereafter. A newer and more refined slim model with higher capacity was released in 2009.

Major features of the console include its free unified online gaming service, the PlayStation Network, its multimedia capabilities, connectivity with the [[PlayStation Portable]], and its use of the Blu-ray Disc as its primary storage medium.
h4. See also
* [[List of game consoles]]

title: playstation_2
body:
The [b]PlayStation 2[/b] (officially abbreviated [b]PS2[/b]) is a [[video game]] home console manufactured by [[Sony]] Computer Entertainment and the successor to the [[PlayStation 1]] as part of the PlayStation series. 

It was first released on March 4, 2000, in [[Japan]], and then was released on October 26, 2000 in North America, and November 24, 2000 in Europe.

The second in Sony's line of PlayStation consoles, developed for the sixth generation market to compete against Microsoft's [[Xbox (original)|]], Nintendo [[GameCube]] and [[Sega Dreamcast]]. The PS2 is hailed as [b]the best selling console of all time[/b], having reached over 154.4 million units sold as of November 21, 2011. As of 2012, over 12 years after its initial release, new games continue to be developed and sold for it. 

h4. See also

title: wii
body:
[[Nintendo]]'s fifth home video [[game console]]. Formerly known as the "Revolution". The original model was released in 2006 and a reconfigured version was released in 2011.

The [b]Wii[/b] competes with [[Sony]]'s [[PlayStation 3]] and [[Microsoft]]'s [[Xbox 360]] as part of the seventh generation of video game consoles. 

The Wii has many advanced features compared to the previous Nintendo consoles. For example, the primary wireless controller, the [[Wii Remote]], can be used as a handheld pointing device and detects movement in three dimensions. Another notable feature of the console is WiiConnect24, which enables it to receive messages and updates over the Internet while in standby mode.

The Wii is Nintendo's fifth home console, and the successor of the Nintendo [[GameCube]], with most models being fully backwardly compatible with all GameCube games and most accessories.

It was succeeded by the [[Wii U]].
h4. See also
* [[List of game consoles]]

title: nintendo_64
body:
[b]Nintendo 64[/b] (stylized as NINTENDO⁶⁴) is [[Nintendo]]'s third home video [[game console]] for the international market. 

Named for its 64-bit central processing unit, it was released in June 1996 in Japan, September 1996 in North America, March 1997 in Europe and Australia, September 1997 in France and December 1997 in Brazil. 

As part of the fifth generation of gaming, it primarily competed with the [[Sony]] [[PlayStation 1]] and the [[Sega Saturn]]. The N64 was discontinued in 2002 in Japan, North America and PAL regions by the launch of Nintendo's [[GameCube]].

It was Nintendo's last home console to use ROM cartridges to store games, until the [[Nintendo Switch]] was released.

h4. See also

* [[List of game consoles]]
* [[Nintendo 64DD]]

title: moroboshi_kirari
body:
An [i][[iDOLMASTER Cinderella Girls|iDOLM@STER Cinderella Girls]][/i] character in the Passion (Yellow Sun) category. She is 17 and is notable for being relatively large compared to the other idols, at 182 cm (5'11.5"). She even continues to grow after training. For comparative purposes, the tallest main character in [[Idolmaster_(classic)|classic]] [i][[Idolmaster_(classic)|iDOLM@STER]][/i] is [[Shijou Takane]] at 169 cm (5'6.5") and the tallest main character in [i][[idolmaster side-m|iDOLM@STER: SideM]][/i] is [[Kurono Genbu]] at 190 cm (6'3"). 

She loves collecting cute things, and has a fun, excitable personality, which is embodied as Kirarin Power, as well as an always-present [[:3]] visage. Fan art often depicts her as being superhumanly strong and prone to accidental destruction.

As one of the most popular [i]Cinderella Girls[/i] characters, she was selected for the second CINDERELLA MASTER CD series, alongside [[Kanzaki Ranko]], [[Maekawa Miku]], [[Jougasaki Mika]] and [[Shimamura Uzuki]]. Her seiyuu is [[Matsuzaki Rei]].

She is in the unit "Ankira" with [[Futaba Anzu]], as well as "[[Decoration (idolmaster)|Decoration]]" with [[Jougasaki Rika]] and [[Akagi Miria]], and their unit costumes are [[Pikapikapop (idolmaster)|]] in the anime.

title: grim_(azur_lane)
body: [[enterprise_(azur_lane)|Enterprise's]] pet eagle in Azur Lane, given to her by her older sister [[yorktown_(azur_lane)|Yorktown]]. Its name varies depending on the server; on CN, its name is "Grim Reaper"; JP, "Eagle-chan", and EN, "Grimmy". Its CN and EN names are derived from USN "Fighting Squadron 10":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VF-10], nicknamed the "Grim Reapers". The naming of Grim is fanon becoming canon, at least for EN. AL's EN playerbase collectively started calling him Grim while still officially being known as "Eagle-chan". In February 2021, a dorm item in the shape of Grim labeled as "Grimmy" was released as a monthly login bonus. Little Enterprise has a comment mentioning "Grimmy". Despite this, the majority of the EN playerbase still refers to him as Grim.

Before her induction into Rhodes Island, she was a college student with two specialties: advanced medical Arts and intervention counseling. Skilled in both medical and combat Arts, she currently works in Rhodes Island's triage section while receiving treatment for her mid-stage Oripathy.

She is on friendly terms with [[Perfumer (Arknights)|]] who regularly assists with her rehabilitation.

Her motif is based on cats. Her callsign is the alter ego that manifests within her, caused by Oripathy. Because of it, she insists to be called by her real name instead.

Her [[voice actor]]s are [[Takahashi Rie]] (JP), Zhang Hong (CN), Triya Leong (EN) and Lee Sae-ah (KR). Her original art designer is [[Lpip]], while her second outfit is drawn by [[Yukuso_(dabiandang)|]] (credited as [[Studio Montagne]] in the game).

title: kasuga_maru_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese escort carrier [i]Kasuga Maru[/i]. Upon remodeling, her name changes to [[Taiyou (kancolle)|]]. Character design by [[Shibafu (glock23)|]], voiced by [[Shuto Yukina]]. 

She has [[long_hair|long]] dark [[brown hair]] in a [[folded ponytail]] held in place with a [[blue_ribbon|blue]] [[hair ribbon]], and [[swept bangs]].  She has [[brown_eyes|brown]] [[tareme]]-style eyes. Similar to [[Akagi (kancolle)|]] and [[Kaga (kancolle)|]], [[Shibafu_(glock23)|]]'s other fleet carriers, she wears a white [[dougi]] top with a red [[hakama short skirt]], and [[black socks]]. On her left hand, she wears a thick falconry [[gloves|glove]].

Her [[rigging]] involves a [[flight deck]] strapped to her right arm, falconry-related steel pouches strapped to her torso, and steel [[platform boots]]. She is notably is modeled upon "classic Japanese falconry":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Takagari] unlike the majority of carriers in-game that are either archers, onmyoji, or marksmen. 

Historically, the [i]Kasuga Maru[/i] was originally built as a [i]Nitta Maru[/i] class passenger-cargo liner, but was requisitioned by the Imperial Japanese Navy and converted into the escort aircraft carrier [i]Taiyou[/i] without ever seeing service as an ocean liner. As [i]Taiyou[/i], she was initially used to transport aircraft and for training, but was later used to escort merchant convoys. She was sunk by a US submarine on August 18, 1944.

One of her lines references "an advertisement":[http://otakei.otakuma.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/210.jpg] where she was anthropomorphized alongside her sister-ships even back in the 1940s. 

Her [[abyssal ship|abyssal]] form is assumed to be the [[Escort Princess]].

title: gundam_exia_repair_iv
body:
Gundam Exia's 4th revision for use by Graham Aker who has joined Celestial Being as a new gundam mister after the events of Gundam 00 A Wakening of the Trailblazer in the stage play gundam 00 festival 10 "re:vision"

It has a return to Exia's original heavy focus on melee with various types of GN blades to fit Graham's fighting style with 2 having built in GN beam guns for ranged combat options

It has a special feature of a localized trans-am to boost the performance of it's left arm(viewers right) while reducing GN particle consumption as Celestial Being is still limited in the amount of functional true GN drives they have post the events second season and the movie, as such it uses a large GN condenser similar of the kind used by GN archer and the gundam 00 condenser type instead of a GN drive thus limiting it operational time.

title: moemi
body:
Moemi is a Female Japanese [[Virtual Youtuber]] who debuted on August 20, 2017. She plays video games and uploads gameplay videos on YouTube. Originating as a character in [[Eilene]]'s [[icetea|series]] "Anime Girl Eilene", she later became [[indie virtual youtuber|independent]], and then on March 26, 2024 she joined [[Aogiri Koukou]]. 

She loves her viewers and calls them "darling". She always starts off her videos by saying "It's your wife, Moemi." She enjoys playing video games and is sometimes emotional and over-reacts to situations. She often cries and becomes depressed by losing in difficult games (such as Dark Souls). When she beats games, she becomes excited and asks her "darling" to pat her hair.

Her YouTube channel can be found here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCy5lOmEQoivK5XK7QCaRKug

title: cable-stayed_bridge
body: Similar to a [[suspension bridge]], this type of bridge also consists of towers or pylons, but rather than a cable being suspended from the towers, multiple cables are anchored directly into the tower and the deck of the bridge. It can easily be distinguished from suspension bridges because all of the cables will be taut and at an angle, rather than vertical and suspended from another cable. Some bridges like the [[Brooklyn Bridge]] are a hybrid of cable-stays and suspension, gaining the benefits of both designs.

title: king_boo_(super_mario_sunshine)
body:
A character from [i][[Super Mario Sunshine]][/i]. He was originally known as "Boss Teresa" (Boss [[Boo (mario)|]]) in Japan, but a sloppy localization resulted in him having the same name as the real [[King Boo]] in the English version.

Despite the uncanny resemblance, Boss Boo isn't really a Boo at all, but rather a product of [[Bowser Jr.]]'s doing, and is made out of goop [tn]"[1]":[https://archive.org/details/super-mario-bros.-encyclopedia-the-official-guide-to-the-first-30-years_202302/page/n107/mode/1up][/tn]. Defining characteristics that set him apart from the real King Boo are his lazy [[aqua eyes]] and ridiculously oversized tongue (which is big even by Boo standards).

title: mu_ren_zhuang
body: A training dummy used in [[wing chun]] [[kung fu]]. Usually made of wood, the typical model takes the form of a sturdy vertical post with several "arms" protruding from the front, vaguely resembling outstretched arms and legs. Practitioners train by striking the "limbs" and body of the dummy in various prescribed ways, building speed and precision. One example of a cinematic use of a [i]mu ren zhuang[/i] can be found in the 1995 [[Jackie Chan]] film [i]Rumble in the Bronx[/i].

body:
[[Honkai (series)|]] sort-of character, tagged under its [[Honkai Impact 3rd]] name, Project Bunny. In [[Benghuai Xueyuan]] it's known as Armored Bunny.

[[Bronya Zaychik]]'s mecha partner in arms utilized for combat. It has the ability to fire cannon shots, concentrated lasers, or cluster missiles. In Honkai Impact 3rd, it takes on a slightly different look depending on which battlesuit Bronya is using. With [[Bronya Zaychik (Wolf's Dawn)|Wolf's Dawn]] Valkyrie form Project Bunny is able to act independently apart from her as its own unit on the field. After Bronya becomes Herrscher of Reason, it becomes able to turn into a [[motorcycle]].

Later down the story in Honkai Impact 3rd, such as in Chapter 36, Project Bunny is given to [[Seele Vollerei]] (post #6181303), and even becomes an obtainable ELF as of version 6.8. This ELF version is voiced by Risa Tsumugi in Japanese.

title: omamori
body:
The popular name used for [[amulet|amulets]] sold in [[Shinto]] [[shrine|shrines]] and Buddhist [[temples]] in Japan. It is said that these amulets have the ability to grant special wishes such as "being successful in a college entrance examination" or "for certain love to come true." 

Although omamoris come in a variety of shapes, their most popular form is a little bag called an お守り袋 ([i]omamori bukuro[/i], omamori pouch) which is a flat pouch with sharp angles, made of vibrant colors containing items that attract good luck. The shape of this pouch was invented by a "[i]Nishijin[/i] textile":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nishijin manufacturer after [[World War II]]. (This company, "Akie Charms Co.,":http://www.akie-net.com/ is still nowadays the largest company in the omamori pouch manufacturing industry.) Nevertheless, omamoris of this type tend to appear frequently in works of fiction set in the Edo period, such as the "[i]jidaigeki[/i].":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jidaigeki 

Often, mothers of students preparing for entrance examinations will make homemade omamoris. In this case, the pouches will have a piece of paper containing a message of encouragement for their children.

* !asset #23731142: An Omamori.

h4.See also

* [[Amulet]]
* [[Ema]]
* [[Ofuda]]
* "Wikipedia article":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Omamori

title: cavalla_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the [i]Gato[/i]-class submarine USS [i]Cavalla[/i] (SS-244). Character designed by [[Suika01]], voiced by [[Kubo Yurika]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] tied in a [[ponytail]] with her [[goggles]] on her head. These goggles also have a snorkel attached. Like her sister [[Albacore (Azur Lane)|]], she is only clad in a [[bikini]] as her default uniform with a single blue [[thigh strap]] on her left leg. Like her sisters, she rides on her submarine rig, with her historical 76 mm single mount used as a [[handgun]].

Historically the submarine responsible for sinking [[Shoukaku (Azur Lane)|]] in the battle of the Philippine Sea, was converted to a hunter-killer submarine post-war before becoming a museum ship in Galveston, Texas.

title: albacore_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the US Navy submarine USS [i]Albacore[/i] (SS-218). Character design by [[Kani Biimu]], voiced by [[Tanezaki Atsumi]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] and [[aqua eyes]], and wears a [[black bikini]] as her default uniform. She also wears red [[wristband|wristbands]] and keeps a 20 mm Oerlikon anti-air gun on her right [[armlet]]. Her 76 mm single mount is holstered [i]on the side of the bikini itself[/i].

She is historically the submarine responsible for sinking [[Taihou (Azur Lane)|]] in the battle of the Philippine Sea, explaining why the latter is fearful of her in the game voice lines (and in [[Azur Lane: Slow Ahead]]).

title: scamp_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the USS [i]Scamp[/i], hull number SS-277, sixty-sixth of seventy-seven Gato-class submarines of the United States Navy.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[grey hair]] with [[side ponytail]], [[black ribbon|black]] [[hair ribbon]] and [[star hair ornament]] and [[grey eyes]]. She wear a [[aqua headwear|aqua]] [[garrison cap]], [[black one-piece swimsuit|black]] [[highleg one-piece swimsuit|highleg]] [[competition swimsuit]], [[white gloves]], torn [[white shorts|white]] [[short shorts]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[rudder footwear]].

Scamp's personality is somewhat synonymous with what her name denotes: Impish and a little sexual. No thanks to her history, however, she is averse to kaiboukan, especially [[Kaiboukan No. 4 (kancolle)|]].

She is the first ever American and Allied submarine in the game as well as the first foreign submarine who never became part of the IJN. As with all American submarines during WWII, she is named after a marine creature, in her case "a species of grouper fish":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scamp_grouper].

She was illustrated by [[Shizuma Yoshinori]].

h4. [i]Gato[/i]-class submarines

title: goblin_slayer
body:
The titular character and main protagonist of [[Goblin Slayer!|Goblin Slayer]]. Also known by his [[elf|elven]] name [b]Orcbolg[/b] (the mighty one).

He is almost always seen wearing [[full armor]] covering his entire body, and even when his helmet is removed his face is kept obscured, thus his full appearance is unknown.

He has an extreme hatred for [[goblin]]s [spoiler]due to his sister being captured, [[rape]]d, and killed by goblins while he could only hide and watch[/spoiler], and for that reason he decided to hunt down and kill all goblins in the world simply out of sheer spite.

h4. External links

title: final_fantasy_vi
body:
Sixth JRPG developed by Square Co., Inc. (now [[Square Enix]]) for the [[Final Fantasy]] series, and one of the most popular games of the series. It was the last Final Fantasy for the SNES, released 2 April 1994. It saw a United States release on 20 October 1994 as [i]Final Fantasy III[/i], as it was the third game in the series to see release there ([[Final Fantasy II|II]], [[Final Fantasy III|III]], and [[Final Fantasy V|V]] weren't released outside Japan at the time, leaving [[Final Fantasy IV|IV]] as the second release and VI as the third). It was later re-released on the PlayStation (1999) and Game Boy Advance (2006), both cases using the game's original title in their English release.

The world is engulfed in a struggle between the Gestahlian Empire, which seeks the Espers - godlike entities of pure magic - to use them to conquer the world and the rebel group Returners. Amidst the conflict, fourteen men and women are also seeking not only an end to the Empire's ambitions, but also the truth of the Espers and the world, all the while stopping [[kefka palazzo|an insane Gestahlian general]] from wreaking havoc.

[i]Final Fantasy VI[/i] is noted for its comparatively large cast of playable characters, somewhat more complex character interactions than was typical for a console RPG at the time, introduction of [[steampunk]] elements to a traditional sword-and-sorcery milieu, a famous [[opera]] scene, and a shocking development about midway through the game in which [spoiler]the villain actually [i]succeeds[/i] in his stated goal of destroying the world.  The remainder of the game is spent traversing a post-apocalyptic version of the world, reuniting your scattered party members in a last-ditch effort to prevent the villain's final takeover.[/spoiler]

title: shining_tears
body:
Shining Tears is a role-playing video game developed by Nextech and published by SEGA released in 2004 in Japan and 2005 in North America for the SONY PlayStation 2.  It is an entry in SEGA's long-running [[shining (series)|Shining series]] of video games. It features character designs and artwork by [[Tony Taka]]. A sequel titled [[Shining Wind]] was released in 2007 with return appearances by all of the main characters of Shining Tears.

An anime adaptation for the game titled Shining Tears X Wind was released in 2007.

title: shining_hearts
body:
A role-playing game developed by Studio Saizensen and published by SEGA. It is the first Shining game to be released for the PlayStation Portable and the third with characters designed by [[Tony Taka]], the other two being [[shining_tears|Shining Tears]] and [[shining_wind|Shining Wind]]. The game was released on December 16, 2010 exclusively in Japan.

The game has been adapted into an anime television series titled Shining Hearts ~Shiawase no Pan~ that premiered in April 2012.

title: swastika
body:
Ancient religious symbol or [[mandala]] used in numerous cultures throughout history ([[India]], etc.). Takes the form of a [[cross]] with four legs bent at 90 degrees.

The clockwise, or right-handed, swastika (卐) was appropriated by the [[nazi|Nazi Party]] as its emblem. This variant was turned 45 degrees in a white circle on a red background which is known as [i]Hakenkreuz[/i] (hooked cross). The symbol continues to be widely associated with Nazism to the present day, and its public display is banned in several countries.

Another user of the clockwise swastika was the [[finland|Finnish]] Air Force, which used a blue swastika for its aircraft insignia from 1918-1944. The [[latvia|Latvian]] Air Force used a dark red version.

The counterclockwise, or left-handed, swastika (卍) is an auspicious symbol in [[Buddhism]] known in Japan as [i]manji[/i].

h4.See also

* [[Kolovrat (symbol)|]]

title: ghost_in_the_shell
body:
[b][i]Ghost in the Shell[/i][/b] ([i]Kōkaku Kidōtai[/i], literally [i]"Mobile Armored Riot Police"[/i]) is a Japanese multimedia [[science fiction]] and [[mecha]] [[cyberpunk]] franchise created in 1989 by [[Shirow Masamune]]. It is comprised of: Shirow's original manga (1989/1991, 2002 and 2003); two animated films (1995 and 2004) directed by Mamoru Oshii; two anime series ([[Ghost in the Shell: Stand Alone Complex]] in 2002-2003 and [i]Ghost in the Shell: S.A.C. 2nd Gig[/i] in 2004-2005), and their sequel OVA ([i]Ghost in the Shell: S.A.C. Solid State Society[/i] in 2006); as well as several video games and novels.

The series focuses on the activities of the counter-terrorist organization [[police|Public Security Section 9]] (公安9課), set in a futuristic, [[cyberpunk]] Japan.

An American live action adaptation was released in [[ghost in the shell (2017)|2017]]. The movie is directed by Rupert Sanders and written by Jamie Moss, William Wheeler and Ehren Kruger. The film stars [[Scarlett Johannson]], [[Kitano Takeshi]], Michael Pitt, Pilou Asbæk, Chin Han and Juliette Binoche. 

h4. Entries
* [[Ghost in the Shell: Innocence]]
* [[Ghost in the Shell 2: Man Machine Interface]]
* [[Ghost in the Shell: Stand Alone Complex]]
** [[Ghost in the Shell: Stand Alone Complex - First Assault Online]]
** [[Ghost in the Shell: SAC 2045]]
* [[Ghost in the Shell Arise]]
* [[Ghost in the Shell (2017)]]

h4. Characters

[b]Main Characters[/b]
* Major [[Kusanagi Motoko]], squad leader of Section 9's anti-terrorist unit
* [[Batou (gits)|]], the major's partner
* [[Togusa (gits)|]], an ex-police inspector

title: nuernberg_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the German light cruiser [i]Nürnberg[/i]. Character design by [[yyy (zelda10010)|yyy]], voiced by [[Toono Hikaru]]. 

She is portrayed with [[very long hair|very long]] [[grey hair]] tied to a single [[braided ponytail]], [[red eyes]], and [[large breasts]]. Her default outfit consists of a [[layered dress]] ([[black dress|black]] outer and [[red dress|red]] inner), [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[black jacket]] with a [[center opening]], [[red necktie]], [[black gloves]], [[black hat]] with [[horns]], [[black thighhighs]] with [[garter straps]], and [[black shoes|black]] [[high heels]]. 

Her [[rigging]] is a mechanical fish containing her 15 cm triple gun mounts and 8.8 cm twin [[anti-aircraft gun]]s. 

h4. Skins

* !post #4290539: Default
* !post #4290538:  [[nuernberg (spring wanderer) (azur lane)|Spring Wanderer]]

h4. History
In real life, [i]Nürnberg[/i] was the second ship of the [i]Leipzig[/i]-class, but had a different profile than [[Leipzig (Azur Lane)|]] herself in that she was 1000 tons heavier, 4 meters (14 feet) longer, 0.05 meters (2 inches) wider, had more AA guns equipped, had a different bridge structure, and different seaplane facilities.

She started her service in the Spanish Civil War on neutrality patrols, then later participated in rather uneventful minelaying and escort activities before becoming a training ship for the rest of the war. Post-war, she was handed over to the Soviet Navy as [i]Admiral Makarov[/i] where she served until 1960 when she was sold for scrap.

h4. [i]Leipzig[/i]-class light cruisers

* [[Leipzig (Azur Lane)|]]
* [b]Nuernberg[/b]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia article":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_cruiser_N%C3%BCrnberg]

title: saitama_(one-punch_man)
body:
The main protagonist character from the [[One-Punch Man]] series.

A 25 years old ridiculously powerful newcomer superhero climbing the ranks of the Hero Organization. Although he is capable of defeating anyone and anything with a single punch, he is overlooked and dismissed by the public and some of the other heroes due to them either misattributing his credit, assuming that his adversaries are very weak, or attributing it to his supposed sheer luck.

Also known as "Caped Baldy", due to his traditional [[superhero costume]] and his [[bald]]ness, the latter [spoiler]the result of the brutal training regime he endured.

body:
A [[science fiction]] series originating from a series of novels written by Itou Keikaku. The series is a trilogy as showed below.

title: aquaman_(dc)
body:
Aquaman superhero from [[DC Comics]]. He's the king of the underwater kingdom of Atlantis, and he has the power to comunicate with and control all sea life. He's also a founding member of the [[Justice League]].

Aquaman's depiction in the [[Super Friends]] tv show is known to have turned him into a laughingstock among the general public, being seen as weak and useless due to his powers only being useful near water. This continued for decades despite writers aiming to depict him in a more serious fashion.
His portrayal by [[Jason Momoa]] in the [[DC Extended Universe]] appears to have put an end to this.

body: The Justice League, or Justice League of America (JLA), is a group of superheroes from [[DC Comics]]. It consists of several of DC's most famous heroes, with their most central members being [[Superman]], [[Batman]],[[Wonder Woman]], [[Green Lantern]], and [[Aquaman (dc)|]].

title: killzone
body:
The [i]Killzone[/i] series of six video games were released from 2004 to 2013 on Sony's [[Playstation 2]], [[Playstation Portable]], [[Playstation 3]], [[Playstation Vita]], and [[Playstation 4]]. The series was the breakout hit for its developer, Guerilla Games Studio. 

In contrast to its primary competition in the form of [[Halo (series)|]] and [[Mass Effect (series)|]], Killzone was noted for having a far more grounded take on future warfare. The entirety of the story is confined to a single star system rather than spanning the whole galaxy, energy weapons are almost (but not entirely) non-existant, and both major factions - the protagonist Interplanetary Strategic Alliance and the antagonist [[Helghast]] - are human. The Helghast's glowing orange goggles, initially a gameplay conceit for visibility on the PS1's limited hardware, gave them a signature recognizable even to those unfamiliar with the Killzone series, as well.

In 2015, Guerilla Games previewed a new game unrelated to previous projects, called [[Horizon (video game)|Horizon: Zero Dawn]], that would wind up being one of the best-selling games on the Playstation 4. The wild success of the Horizon series dealt the effective end to Killzone.

title: muzzle_gag
body: A [[gag]] worn to keep the subject's mouth closed by pulling on the chin or jaw. Similar to a [[panel gag]] it consists of a panel that covers the wearer's mouth and is reinforced with a [[gag harness]], but with a more mask-like design that covers the user's chin and often cheeks.

title: cave_(developer)
body:
Japanese video game company founded in 1994 primarily associated with shoot 'em ups. Since 1995, CAVE has been one of the most prolific shoot 'em up developers in the Japanese market. They have released games for arcade machines, home consoles, PCs and smartphones.

title: kaminari_clara
body:
[[Phase Connect]] talent for their Japanese generation 1 group, "[[Phase KALEiDO]]".

h4. Appearance
[tn]See post #7177552 for the reference sheet.[/tn]
She is portrayed with [[long_hair|long]], [[blue hair]] with [[blonde_hair|blonde]] [[streaked_hair|streaks]], [[blue eyes]] with [[lightning_bolt-shaped_pupils|lightning bolt pupils]], [[fangs]] and [[medium breasts]]. Her default hairstyle has [[sidelocks|long sidelocks]] and a [[side_ponytail|long side ponytail]].

Her default outfit is a [[playboy bunny]] outfit, wearing [[fake_animal_ears|fake]] [[rabbit ears]] and a [[black_headwear|black]] [[top hat]], accessorized with [[dice]] and [[playing_card|playing cards]], a [[blue_ribbon|blue]] [[hair ribbon]], a [[frilled_collar|frilled]] [[blue collar]], a [[blue_bowtie|blue]] and [[black bowtie]] with a [[spade brooch]], blue [[arm_garter|arm garters]], a [[double-breasted]] [[white leotard]] worn over a black [[bodystocking]], with a [[rabbit tail]] and [[blue bow]], and [[black_footwear|black]] [[high heels]] adorned with [[blue_bow|blue]] [[footwear_bow|bows]] and [[pom_pom_(clothes)|pom poms]]. 
She can also alternately wear a [[black_mask|black]] [[domino mask]] with opaque lenses and a [[lightning bolt hair ornament]].

title: pretty_guardian_sailor_moon
body:
A live-action [[tokusatsu]] TV show based on the manga series [[Bishoujo Senshi Sailor Moon]]. The series was produced by Toei, who also produces the [[Kamen Rider]] and [[Super Sentai]] series. During its run Naoko rebooted the manga series under the name of the TV title.

The costumes worn by the actors are noticeably closer to [[Takeuchi Naoko]]'s original manga design. To transform, they use the [[Jewelry Star Bracelet]], instead of sticks as seen in the anime. The bracelet has a pink band with a silver heart.

One of the actresses, Kitagawa Keiko, plays as [[Hino Rei]]/[[Sailor Mars]] in the series. Later on, she voices [[Sailor Cosmos]] in [[Bishoujo Senshi Sailor Moon Crystal]].

h4. See also

* [[Sailor Moon Musical]] (theater production)

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Pretty Guardian Sailor Moon (2003 TV series)":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pretty_Guardian_Sailor_Moon_(2003_TV_series)]

title: dual_persona
body:
Two different versions of the same character appearing together in the same scene. Example: [[Saber (fate)|]] & [[Saber Alter]].

If the picture depicts them as two distinct characters in the same scene, don't use [[solo]], [[1girl]] or [[1boy]] with this tag. Exceptions are [[split theme]], [[multiple views]], [[creature and personification]] and similar themes.

When the character is meeting their [[aged up|older]] or [[aged down|younger]] self, also tag [[age comparison]] if the personas have no interactions, or [[time paradox]] if the personas have interactions other than posing for the camera.

If the instances of the character are identical, use [[clone]] instead. If more than two personae are in one image, use [[multiple persona]] instead.



h4. See also

* [[age comparison]]
* [[dark persona]]
* [[doppelganger]]
* [[look-alike]]
* [[selfcest]]
* [[clone harem]]

title: multiple_persona
body: Similar to [[dual persona]], except that there at least three personas of the same character involved. Take note that the [[solo]] tag, or singular people counters ([[1boy]], [[1girl]], [[1other]]) should [b]not[/b] be used with this tag. If the instances of the character are identical, use [[clone]] instead. Also see [[time paradox]] and [[multiple expressions]]. Do not use the tag for [[reference sheet]], [[variations]] and other depictions of the same character from different points of view (unless those are really different persona as in post #1173905). h4. See also * [[selfcest]] * [[clone harem]] * [[time paradox]]

title: slime_taoshite_300_nen_shiranai_uchi_ni_level_max_ni_nattemashita
body:
A light novel and webnovel series authored by Morita Kisetsu and illustrated by [[benio (dontsugel)|benio]]. In English, the title is "I've unknowingly become max level after defeating slimes for 300 years."

[quote]
※２０１７年４月１５日ＧＡノベルさん２巻発売します！ 皆さんのおかげです！
ごく普通の社畜ＯＬ、相沢梓は働きすぎが原因で過労死した。
そのため、１７歳の容姿を持つ不老不死の魔女として、高原の一軒家でスローライフを送ることにした。
主な収入源は近くに生息するスライムを倒して魔法石を手に入れること。これをふもとの村のギルドで売っていた。ほかにも、薬草の知識を使って薬を作ってあげたりして、「高原の魔女」として感謝され、敬意を集めて生きていた。

だが、３００年もスライムを倒す生活を続けてきた結果、経験値が蓄積しすぎて、知らないうちにレベル９９の世界最強の魔女となっていたことが発覚。

レベル９９の魔女は今日も村のみんなのため、世の中のために、弟子のドラゴン少女とともにほどほどに働きます。
[/quote]

Translation:

[quote]
[[Aizawa Azusa]], a very ordinary office lady, died due to overwork.

For that reason, she decided to live a leisurely life in an isolated home near a plateau as an immortal witch with the appearance of a 17 year old.

Her main source of income is defeating slimes and acquiring their magic stones. She sells these stones at the guild of the village near the base of the mountain. Besides that, she also makes medicine from her knowledge of medicinal herbs. She came to be known as "The Witch of the Plateau" (高原の魔女) for the honor and gratitude she has been given for her efforts.

However, as a result of continuing life defeating slimes for 300 years, she accumulated too much experience and before she knew it, it came to light she was the world's strongest witch at Level 99.

A story about a Level 99 witch working together with her dragon girl disciple for the sake of everyone in the village, and for the world.
[/quote]

h4.Characters

title: giygas
body:
The final boss of the video games [[mother_1|Mother]] and [[Mother 2]]. Known as Gyiyg in the original.

In the first game, his appearance was of a grayish alien. In the second game, his appearance changed drastically, becoming one swirling red face which appears to be screaming.

He is best known for the [[mind rape]] his appearance and attacks in Mother 2 causes, spawning the line "You cannot grasp the true form of Giygas' attack".

h4. See also
* [[Giegue]]
* Wikipedia's article on Giygas: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Giygas

title: mother_1
body:
The first game in [[MOTHER (series)|]] series from [[Nintendo]] by Itoi Shigesato, released for the [[Famicom|Family Computer]] on July 27, 1989.

This game was translated but unreleased in North America for some time, leaving a prototype. On June 20, 2003, this game was re-released in Japan for the [[Game Boy Advance]] along with [[MOTHER 2]] in a 2-in-1 game, [i]MOTHER 1+2[/i]. On June 14, 2015, the translated version was released internationally under the title [i]EarthBound Beginnings[/i].

title: oozora_subaru_(starlight)
body:
The 6th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Oozora Subaru]]. This costume is largely based on her [[Oozora subaru (work)|2nd costume]] with an [[idol]] motif, it was revealed during her 4th anniversary 3D live in November 2022.

It consists of a [[white hat|white]] [[beret]] with a [[sunflower hair ornament]], an [[orange shirt|orange]] [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[cropped shirt]] with a [[vertical-striped shirt|vertical]] [[pinstripe shirt|pinstripe pattern]] and [[white shirt|white]] [[frilled shirt|frilled]] [[undershirt]] with [[center frills]] underneath,  2 bowties (a[[white bowtie|white]] [[striped bowtie|striped]] one and a [[black bowtie|black]] one under it) held with a [[flower brooch]], a grey [[underbust]] [[corset]], [[white gloves|white]] [[frilled gloves]], [[black shorts]] with [[suspenders]] and a [[hip vent]] showing her [[orange panties]], a [[green sash]] with a [[floral bow|floral]] [[waist bow]], a [[layered skirt|layered]] [[overskirt]] with an outer [[orange skirt|orange]] [[vertical-striped skirt|vertical-striped]] [[pinstripe skirt]] and a [[white skirt|white]] [[frilled skirt]] underneath, a [[large bow|large]] [[back bow]], [[white thighhighs|white]] [[argyle thighhighs]] with [[white garter straps]] and [[black footwear|black]] [[high heel boots]].

She has 2 different [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyles]] in this costume
* [[Short hair]] with [[swept bangs]]
* [[Long hair|Long]] [[straight hair]] also with swept bangs

body: Alea jacta est (notice the typo) is an album reference in maimai dx that draws on the ancient Latin phrase meaning “the die is cast.” Traditionally linked to Julius Caesar’s decisive Rubicon crossing, it now symbolizes a bold, irreversible step.

title: achilles_(mythology)
body: A legendary hero of the Trojan War from [[Greek mythology]]. Famous for having been a mighty warrior and impervious to harm in all places but his heel, giving rise to the 'Achilles tendon' as well as a person's fatal weakness being referred to as one's 'Achilles heel', as he is ultimately slain by an arrow to his heel.

title: 0011_(cyborg_009)
body: Cyborg 0011 is a giant, black-colored, mechanical spider-like cyborg. Is an enormous cyborg with a circular body and six mechanical legs, mimicking the appearance of a spider. The sides of his body are entirely lined by small windows that glow blue and fitted with turrets. His feet, like Jet Link, are fitted with a high-quality jet propulsion system that allows him to fly.

title: sideways_mouth
body:
A quirk of manga/anime art where a character's face is viewed [[profile|from the side]], yet their mouth is drawn on the side of their face, rather than on the front. 

Often the lips are still drawn on the front of the face, making it appear as if the character has two mouths.

One reason this may be done is to show more of the character's facial expression when it wouldn't otherwise be visible. Another reason is that, in animation, it's faster and easier to draw the mouth on the side than to animate the entire mouth opening normally, which would include having to adjust the jawline and lips.

For mouths that are [i]literally[/i] sideways (rotated from the position of a regular mouth by 90°), use [[vertical mouth]].

title: deel
body: A deel is a traditional [[mongolian clothes|mongolian]] coat/dress worn by Mongolian and Turkic people. It is long, usually reaching below the knees and with long sleeves. It is similar in its side buttoning to [[china dress|qipao]], but can also have a [[fold-over collar]].

title: tangzhuang
body:
A [b]tangzhuang[/b] (Simplified Chinese: 唐装) is a kind of pseudo-traditional Chinese [[jacket]], typically with a [[mandarin collar]].

It originated at the end of the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911) as an evolution of the Manchurian [i]magua[/i], which had been adopted by the Han Chinese during the [[Qing Dynasty]]. At that time, only noblemen, aristocracy and government officials wore it, however, in modern times it was eventually adopted by common people. This kind of clothing is often seen as a national costume for men, although women wear it as well. 

[[Saotome Ranma]] from [[Ranma 1/2]] is usually seen wearing this type of jacket.

h4. See also

* [[chinese clothes]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Tangzhuang":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangzhuang]
* "GBTimes: The tang suit and its Qing Dynasty origins":[https://gbtimes.com/tang-suit-and-its-qing-dynasty-origins]

title: hololive
body:
Hololive (stylized as "hololive") is an all-female [[virtual YouTuber|VTuber]] group managed by Hololive Production, which itself is owned and operated by Cover Corp.

As of September 2023, the hololive group consists of 4 major branches: the original Japanese-speaking branch (unofficially referred to as Hololive Japan), the other Japanese-speaking branch [[hololive DEV_IS]], [[hololive Indonesia]], and [[hololive English]]. (There was also the now-disbanded [[hololive China]].) Each branch is further divided into multiple generations, where each generation is a batch of VTubers who debuted at the same time. Hololive Production also manages the all-male counterpart group [[Holostars]].

In February 2021, Cover announced [[hololive Alternative]], a multimedia project including several manga and music videos that aims to tell in-universe stories using the hololive VTubers' character backstories. Later, in August 2021, Cover announced [[hololive Error]], a horror-themed spin-off project. A year later, in June 2022, Cover announced [[Holoearth]], a game featuring various hololive members. In March 2023, Cover announced [[Blue Journey (hololive)|]], a new musical project.

h4. List of Members

h5. hololive (original branch, [i]a.k.a.[/i] hololive Japan)

h6. hololive "[[0th Generation (hololive)|]]"

A term for the members not under a specific grouping. Some of these members debuted as independents and were initially brought into other now-defunct branches of the company before joining Hololive proper.

* [[Tokino Sora]] (debuted September 2017)
* [[Roboco-san]] (debuted March 2018)
* [[Hoshimachi Suisei]] (debuted as indie in March 2018, joined the company in May 2019, joined Hololive in December 2019)
* [[Sakura Miko]] (debuted August 2018, joined Hololive in December 2018)

title: elemental_(creature)
body:
A broad class of mythological creature associated with the classical Greek elements: [[earth_(element)|earth]], [[water]], air, and [[fire]]. The concept of elementals originated in Renaissance-era European [[alchemy|alchemical]] works but has been popularized in recent decades by [[Dungeons & Dragons]] and related [[fantasy]] settings.

Depictions of elementals vary widely but they tend to be roughly humanoid in appearance, with abilities and personality traits corresponding to their associated elements. For instance, water elementals are adaptable and can flow like liquid, whereas fire elementals are passionate and can burn anything they touch.

Occasionally, elementals may be associated with "elements" other than the usual four. For instance, ice elementals, lightning elementals, or plant elementals.

title: healin'_good_precure
body:
The seventeenth installment of the [[Precure]] series, released in 2020. It primarily focuses on animals. It is also the very first Precure title fully released in the [[Reiwa]] era, as [[Star Twinkle Precure]] was released in late [[Heisei]].

The Healin' Garden, a secret world where Earth is healed, is under attack by the Byougenzu, who are trying to infect the Earth.
In order to salve it, three medical trainees of Earth, the Healin' Animals, along with Latte, the little princess of the Healin' Garden who holds a special power, escaped in search of their partners!
Now, three ordinary girls are able to transform into Pretty Cure with the power of the Healin' Animals and fight against the Byougenzu!
The Pretty Cure are in charge of defending Latte and the precious Earth and all her creatures by taking care of them.

[b]Orie Ballardiae (オリエ・バラーディア)[/b], known by her Japanese alias as [b]"Harada Orie" (原田織依)[/b], is a character in [[Under Night In-Birth]]. She is an Executor of Licht Kreis who sent to investigate the high influx of In-Birth activity in Kanzakai.

She is sent on an undercover mission by Zenith in order to keep an eye on Amnesia's activities. At the same time she continues her studies in the same school as [[Kido hyde|Hyde]].

Her parents were murdered by a Void when she was young, it's one of many reasons she fights to protect people from the dangers of the Hollow Night. title: set_(mythology)
body:
In [[Egyptian mythology]], [b]Set[/b] is the [[fox]]-headed* god of the desert, storms and foreigners, later reinterpreted as a god of evil, dark magic, and darkness.

Set is usually depicted as a villain is several myths and an arch-nemesis of [[Horus (mythology)|]]. His antics were used to explain various phenomena within [[ancient Egyptian]] culture, such as his killing of [[Osiris (mythology)|]] that became the origin story of [[mummy|mummification]].

[tn]*He is sometimes depicted with the head of an [[aardvark]] or an unknown "'Set animal'":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Set_animal] instead.[/tn]

title: sandalphon_(granblue_fantasy)
body:
A [[Granblue Fantasy]] character. Voiced by [[suzumura_ken'ichi|Suzumura Ken'ichi]] in Japanese and Howard Wang in English.

Having arisen from a deep, long slumber, this archangel has inherited the will of the supreme primarch, [[lucifer_(shingeki_no_bahamut)|Lucifer]]. Though [[sandalphon_(granblue_fantasy)|Sandalphon]] previously had no role to play, he now bears the burden of carrying out vengeance in hopes of fulfilling a promise. Debuting as the central antagonist of the event "What Makes The Sky Blue" in 2017, [[sandalphon_(granblue_fantasy)|Sandalphon]] was originally intended as a simple one-off villain for an anniversary event. His popularity with the players, however, caused Cygames to turn WMTSB into a trilogy of events, with him starring in both the second and third parts, being recruitable in both.

He has gained several alternate forms due to his popularity, including a [https://gbf.wiki/Sandalphon_(Summer)](Water Summer) version in 2019, an [https://gbf.wiki/Sandalphon_(Earth_Grand)](Earth Grand) version in 2020, a [https://gbf.wiki/Sandalphon_(Valentine)](Wind Valentines) version in 2023, and a [https://gbf.wiki/Sandalphon](Light Grand) version in 2024. Currently, he is the only playable character to possess two distinct Grand forms. 

During the 10th Anniversary stream, it was revealed that he would join the roster of playable characters in [[granblue_fantasy:_relink|Granblue Fantasy: Relink]] in May 2024. Later, during EVO 2024, it was announced that he would also be added to [[granblue_fantasy_versus:_rising|Granblue Fantasy Versus: Rising]] as part of Character Pass Season 2 in 2025.

title: lacey_games
body:
Animated web series created by Brazilian artist [[ghosttundra]] taking place in the 2000's, revolving around a collection of fictional [[flash]] games in which a girl named [[Lacey (Lacey Games)|]] is ordered to perform mundane tasks, usually with unexpected horror twists such as [spoilers][[Lacey (Lacey Games)|]] being murdered or stalked[/spoilers]. The show has an intentionally childish art-style which imitates the anime-esque [[2000s (style)|art styles]] which were prominent in the west in the 2000's.

title: blind
body:
Refers to a character who cannot use their eyes for sight. Either depicted with a [[blindfold]], completely [[closed eyes]], a pitch [[white eyes]] with the lack of pupils, or even [[blank eyes|completely blanked eyes]].

Note that this tag is only for when a character can be [i]visually[/i] identified to be blind, such as them holding a [[white cane]], having a [[scar across eye|scar across their eyes]], of the lack of defined pupils. Do not apply this tag simply because it feature characters who is canonically blind (such as [[Toph Beifong]]) unless there is evidence suggesting their blindedness.

h4. Examples
* !post #6227865: A typical example of a blind person, evident by their lack of pupils, the [[white cane]], and a [[guide dog]].
* !post #7951609: Blindness that is evident by a [[scar across eye]].

h4. Related tags

* [[guide dog]]

title: lost_sword:_tales_of_britania
body:
A 2D autobattler gacha game developed by Code Cat and published by Wemade Connect. It officially released in South Korea on January 16, 2025.

[b]"Lost Sword"[/b] is an isekai narrative loosely based around the [[Arthurian legend]]. Players mainly follow a 4-person party traveling the continent of Britannia to find a legendary sword named [[Excalibur (mythology)|]]. This party consists of:

* Ethan - The player character. He is a South Korean jobseeker who found himself in Britannia due to mysterious circumstances. He currently holds the title of Swordbringer, a chosen one who would assist the rightful wielder of the Excalibur in their search for it.
* [[Elizabeth Pendragon (Lost Sword)|]] - Daughter of former Britannian king Uther Pendragon and an analogue for [[King Arthur]]. She is searching for Excalibur in order to use its power to take back the kingdom from the hands of the kingslayer and betrayer Vortigern.
* [[Morgana (Lost Sword)|]] - The Fairy Queen and an analogue for [[Morgan le Fay]]. She is currently accompanying Ethan due to his role as the Swordbringer. Much older than her peers due to her having the ability to endlessly reincarnate upon death, but she's become a bit of a NEET due to some of her experiences.
* [[Bedivere (Lost Sword)|]] - Elizabeth's retainer and closest friend. Ditzy and kind of gullible, but her expertise with the bow and arrow and her healing magic makes her a powerful ally to the party.

title: johnston_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the USS [I]Johnston[/i] (hull number DD-557), 75th of the US Navy's 175 Fletcher-class destroyers.

h4. Appearance

In comparison to [[samuel b. roberts (kancolle)|Samuel B. Roberts]], Johnston is depicted as much taller and [[medium_breasts|slightly more well-endowed]] with [[long_hair|long]] pinkish [[light brown hair]] tied into a [[two side up]] style and [[brown eyes]].

She wears a stylized [[serafuku]] which consists of an [[off shoulder|off-shoulder]] [[blue shirt]] with a black [[sailor collar]] that exposes her [[cleavage]] and short [[black skirt|black]] [[pleated skirt]], along with [[black thighhighs]] held by [[garter straps]] with what seem to be metallic thigh and [[shin guards]] and red [[rudder footwear|rudder shoes]]. Johnston's damaged CG has her stripped of some of her clothing, revealing a bit of her black underwear.

On her left hand she wears a [[single glove|single]] [[black gloves|black glove]], an oblique reference to the injuries to the left hand sustained by her captain, "Lieutenant Commander Ernest E. Evans":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ernest_E._Evans], including losing two fingers. Draped on her left upper arm is the [[united states medal of honor|Medal of Honor]], presumably similar to the one posthumously awarded to Lieutenant Commander Evans for his actions in the "Battle off Samar":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_off_Samar].

Her [[machinery]] consists of two [[smokestack]]s and two 5-inch [[cannon]] [[ship turret|turret]]s with one set on each side of her rigging, with a third [[adapted turret|handheld turret]] on her right hand. Her hull number is emblazoned on each side of her lower rigs.

h4. Personality

She is often compared to [[amatsukaze (kancolle)|Amatsukaze]] due to both having similar [[two side up]] hairstyles and sailor outfits with gartered thighhighs as well as apparently sharing similar [[tsundere]] personalities.

h4. History

The historical destroyer was part of the Taffy 3 party (which included [[samuel b. Roberts (kancolle)|Samuel B. Roberts]] and [[gambier bay (kancolle)|Gambier Bay]]) and was sunk during the "Battle off Samar":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_off_Samar] by successive firings from Kurita Takeo's forces, but not before scoring hits of her own, including those to [[kumano (kancolle)|Kumano]]. For her actions, she was given a Presidential Unit Citation and six battle stars, which shipgirl Johnston displays as one bronze star and one silver star (equivalent to five bronzes) on her collar.

h4. Trivia

She's voiced by "Shiraki Nao":https://myanimelist.net/people/42439 and was designed by [[Zeco]]. Her namesake is "Navy Lieutenant John V. Johnston":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_V._Johnston], who fought for the Union from 1862 to 1864 during the American Civil War. She is the game's first bona fide American destroyer, despite the fact that destroyer escort [[samuel b. roberts (kancolle)|Samuel B. Roberts]] was already classified as a destroyer in the game.

title: inglis_eucus
body:
Female protagonist of the series [[Eiyuuou bu wo Kiwameru Tame Tenseisu: Soshite Sekai Saikyou no Minarai Kishi|Eiyuu-ou bu wo Kiwameru Tame Tensei su ~Soshite Sekai Saikyou no Minarai Kishi ♀~]] (English title: Reborn to Master the Blade: From Hero-King to Extraordinary Squire ♀).

Inglis Eucus, nicknamed  Chris (クリス Kurisu), is a young lady with [[red eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] silver hair.  In her previous life she was the Hero-King Inglis who was blessed by a goddess and tasked with leading the people to build a great nation.  Regretting that the potential of his blessing was wasted in his life achieving the goddess' task, the goddess granted him another chance at life so that he could strive to unlock the full potential of his blessing as a warrior.

When it was determined that Inglis was a "runeless" during her baptismal ceremony and that would bar her from becoming a knight due to (normally) lacking the ability to wield an artifact weapon, she chose to become her childhood friend and first cousin [[Rafinha Bilford|Rafinha Bilford's]] knight squire. Although for Inglis this was her desired outcome.

Inglis and Rafinha, like their mothers, are very big eaters.

"Inglis on Wiki Fandom":[https://reborn-to-master-the-blade-from-heroking-to-squire.fandom.com/wiki/Inglis_Eucus]

title: carmine_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Carmine[/b], known as [b]Zeiyu[/b] (ゼイユ ) in Japan, is a character from [[Pokemon sv|Pokémon Scarlet and Violet]]'s expansions "The Teal Mask" and "The Indigo Disk".

She was born in Kitakami and is a student at Blueberry Academy. She is the older sister of [[kieran (pokemon)|Kieran.]]

She has [[long hair|long]], [[two-tone hair]] that is [[black hair|black]] and [[red hair|red]]. The latter color making up her [[colored inner hair]]. Her [[crossed bangs]] go [[hair between eyes|between her eyes]]. She has a [[mole under eye|mole under]] her [[yellow eyes]]. She usually wears a [[yellow hairband]].

title: wang_wei_(pla_pilot)
body:
A pilot of the [[People's Liberation Army Air Force]]. On April 1, 2001, he was sent to intercept a Lockheed EP-3 signals intelligence aircraft in his [[Shenyang J-8]] (No. 81192 or 81194) alongside another pilot over Hainan. After making two close passes by the EP-3, he collided with it the third time, breaking his aircraft in two and possibly killing him.
h4. See also
* "Wikipedia: Hainan Island Incident":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hainan_Island_incident]
